# Llama 3.3 70B on TPU v7x (TP=8) — extreme prefill-heavy 32K in / 1 out.
#
# Successor to llama3_8b/prefill_heavy.workload, scaled up on two axes:
# (a) bigger model — on TPUs, decode is bandwidth-bound but prefill is
#     compute-bound, so prefill's share of total time grows with model
#     size. K-servings relative gain is expected to grow with it.
# (b) longer context — 32K input has 4x more chunks (at K=256: 128 vs
#     32) for the static-K PREFILL kernel to amortize launch overhead
#     over.
#
# Architecture (verified from HF config.json):
#   64 q-heads / 8 kv-heads (GQA 8x) / head_dim=128 / 80 layers / bf16.
# Native context 128K; we cap at 32K because 32K is where the
# real-world long-context demand currently sits (RAG with many docs,
# long agent traces) and tuning a 128K shape would 4x the kernel
# search space without a customer driving it.
#
# Sizing math at TP=8 v7x:
#   Weights        : 70B × 2B / 8 = 17.5 GB / chip
#   KV per token   : 2 × 8 × 128 × 2 × 80 = 320 KB (all layers)
#   KV per request : 32K × 320 KB = 10.5 GB total / 1.3 GB / chip
#   v7x HBM        : 192 GB / chip — comfortable headroom for 64+ seqs.

: "${MODEL:=meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct}"
: "${TENSOR_PARALLEL_SIZE:=8}"
: "${NUM_Q_HEADS:=64}"
: "${NUM_KV_HEADS:=8}"
: "${HEAD_DIM:=128}"

: "${MAX_NUM_SEQS:=64}"
: "${MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS:=8192}"
: "${MAX_MODEL_LEN:=32768}"

# vLLM --block-size (KV-cache page size). LEFT EMPTY because no
# kernel tune exists yet for the (70B shape, 32K context) TuningKey.
# Layer 1 of the orchestrator will tune all three page_size options
# (64, 128, 256) for this new shape; auto-link will then inject the
# winner here for the full sweep. Direct one-shot runs without the
# sweep will use vLLMs default.
: "${BLOCK_SIZE:=}"

: "${DATASET:=sonnet}"
: "${INPUT_LEN:=32767}"
: "${OUTPUT_LEN:=1}"
# 200 prompts (vs 1000 for 8B): at the slower per-request rate
# expected for 70B, 1000 prompts would push the bench past 30 min
# per combo and make the 48-combo sweep unreasonably long.
: "${NUM_PROMPTS:=200}"
